{"article_id":"yeHJvL3eNdJl6jn2","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"A man with a shotgun and a beef against his local newspaper stalked into the offices of the Annapolis Capital Gazette on Thursday","depth":8},{"id":1,"text":"and opened fire on the newsroom ,","depth":8},{"id":2,"text":"killing five people","depth":8},{"id":3,"text":"and wounding two others ,","depth":8},{"id":4,"text":"police said .","depth":6},{"id":5,"text":"Police called it a \" targeted attack , \"","depth":7},{"id":6,"text":"saying","depth":8},{"id":7,"text":"the gunman had sent threats to the newspaper on social media","depth":9},{"id":8,"text":"and entered the building","depth":10},{"id":9,"text":"looking for specific people .","depth":10},{"id":10,"text":"\" This person was prepared to shoot people , \"","depth":8},{"id":11,"text":"said William Krampf , acting chief for the Anne Arundel County Police Department .","depth":8},{"id":12,"text":"\" His intent was to cause harm . \"","depth":7},{"id":13,"text":"The chief identified the gunman only as a white male in his late 30s .","depth":5},{"id":14,"text":"The Baltimore Sun ,","depth":8},{"id":15,"text":"which owns the Capital Gazette ,","depth":8},{"id":16,"text":"identified the suspected gunman as Jarrod W. Ramos , a 38-year-old Laurel resident","depth":8},{"id":17,"text":"who unsuccessfully filed a defamation lawsuit in 2012 against the paper over coverage of a criminal harassment case against him .","depth":8},{"id":18,"text":"Other news outlets reported similarly .","depth":7},{"id":19,"text":"Former Capital Gazette publisher and editor Tom Marquardt told The Sun on Thursday night","depth":9},{"id":20,"text":"that \" I remember telling our attorneys ,","depth":10},{"id":21,"text":"' This is a guy","depth":11},{"id":22,"text":"who is going to come in","depth":12},{"id":23,"text":"and shoot us. ' \"","depth":12},{"id":24,"text":"\" Marquardt said","depth":10},{"id":25,"text":"he considered a restraining order","depth":11},{"id":26,"text":"and asked police to intervene in 2013 , \"","depth":11},{"id":27,"text":"Sun reporter Erin Cox said on Twitter .","depth":9},{"id":28,"text":"SEE ALSO :","depth":4},{"id":29,"text":"Capital Gazette shooting suspect kept to himself ,","depth":5},{"id":30,"text":"' played a lot of war video games '","depth":5},{"id":31,"text":"Police identified the dead","depth":8},{"id":32,"text":"- all Capital Gazette employees -","depth":8},{"id":33,"text":"at a Thursday night news conference .","depth":7},{"id":34,"text":"They were Wendi Winters , special publications editor ; Rob Hiaasen , editor and Sunday columnist ; John McNamara , writer ; Gerald Fischman , editorial page editor ; and Rebecca Smith , sales assistant .","depth":6},{"id":35,"text":"According to Selene San Felice , a reporter with the Capital Gazette","depth":8},{"id":36,"text":"who spoke to CNN on Thursday evening ,","depth":8},{"id":37,"text":"the gunman ,","depth":9},{"id":38,"text":"whom she did not recognize ,","depth":9},{"id":39,"text":"targeted the newspaper ' s editors .","depth":8},{"id":40,"text":"\" That ' s what happened here .","depth":8},{"id":41,"text":"Editors died .","depth":9},{"id":42,"text":"It ' s just a fact , \"","depth":9},{"id":43,"text":"she said ,","depth":8},{"id":44,"text":"trying to keep her composure .","depth":8},{"id":45,"text":"Authorities said","depth":7},{"id":46,"text":"it took only about a minute to respond to the shooting","depth":8},{"id":47,"text":"and they took the suspect into custody","depth":9},{"id":48,"text":"without exchanging fire .","depth":9},{"id":49,"text":"They cleared the building ,","depth":7},{"id":50,"text":"evacuating about 170 people ,","depth":8},{"id":51,"text":"and found smoke grenades in the process .","depth":8},{"id":52,"text":"\" It ' s a tragic situation ,","depth":7},{"id":53,"text":"but there were some very brave people","depth":9},{"id":54,"text":"who came in","depth":9},{"id":55,"text":"and kept it from being worse , \"","depth":8},{"id":56,"text":"Maryland Gov . Larry Hogan said .","depth":6},{"id":57,"text":"Defiant survivors of the attack vowed to continue their work .","depth":5},{"id":58,"text":"\" I can tell you this :","depth":7},{"id":59,"text":"We are putting out a damn paper tomorrow , \"","depth":7},{"id":60,"text":"reporter Chase Cook tweeted .","depth":6},{"id":61,"text":"The newspaper ' s staff took to Twitter","depth":9},{"id":62,"text":"to share details of the assault ,","depth":9},{"id":63,"text":"describing the gunman as shooting through the glass doors to the office ,","depth":9},{"id":64,"text":"then opening fire on employees .","depth":9},{"id":65,"text":"\" There is nothing more terrifying","depth":9},{"id":66,"text":"than hearing multiple people get shot","depth":11},{"id":67,"text":"while you ' re under your desk","depth":11},{"id":68,"text":"and then hear the gunman reload , \"","depth":10},{"id":69,"text":"tweeted reporter Phil Davis .","depth":8},{"id":70,"text":"Other reporters also went on the social media site","depth":10},{"id":71,"text":"to let family and friends know","depth":12},{"id":72,"text":"they were safe","depth":12},{"id":73,"text":"- and to plead for solitude .","depth":11},{"id":74,"text":"\" Devastated & heartbroken .","depth":12},{"id":75,"text":"Numb .","depth":12},{"id":76,"text":"Please stop asking for information/interviews .","depth":12},{"id":77,"text":"I ' m in no position","depth":13},{"id":78,"text":"to speak , \"","depth":13},{"id":79,"text":"said Jimmy DeButts , community news editor and columnist at the paper .","depth":10},{"id":80,"text":"He added :","depth":9},{"id":81,"text":"\" We try to expose corruption .","depth":11},{"id":82,"text":"We fight to get access to public records","depth":15},{"id":83,"text":"& bring to light the inner workings of government","depth":15},{"id":84,"text":"despite major hurdles","depth":15},{"id":85,"text":"put in our way .","depth":15},{"id":86,"text":"The reporters & editors put their all into finding the truth .","depth":13},{"id":87,"text":"That is our mission .","depth":13},{"id":88,"text":"Will always be , \"","depth":13},{"id":89,"text":"he tweeted .","depth":10},{"id":90,"text":"The 30,000-circulation daily has offices in a building on the outskirts of downtown Annapolis .","depth":9},{"id":91,"text":"It shares the building with other professional offices ,","depth":11},{"id":92,"text":"and people in those offices described a harrowing ordeal .","depth":11},{"id":93,"text":"\" Terrifying , \"","depth":12},{"id":94,"text":"said Lacy McKinney , 32 ,","depth":13},{"id":95,"text":"who works at Chesapeake Cardiac Care .","depth":13},{"id":96,"text":"\" I finally got my hands to stop shaking","depth":14},{"id":97,"text":"after being released","depth":15},{"id":98,"text":"after being questioned by the police , \"","depth":15},{"id":99,"text":"she told The .","depth":13},{"id":100,"text":"\" You never think","depth":13},{"id":101,"text":"you ' ll wake up one day","depth":14},{"id":102,"text":"and see the police with big guns","depth":15},{"id":103,"text":"yelling","depth":16},{"id":104,"text":"and screaming","depth":17},{"id":105,"text":"to get your hands up . \"","depth":17},{"id":106,"text":"At a McDonald ' s near the paper , workers were telling customers to stay","depth":10},{"id":107,"text":"rather than go home","depth":10},{"id":108,"text":"because \" it ' s not safe out there . \"","depth":9},{"id":109,"text":"Police said","depth":8},{"id":110,"text":"in addition to the five dead , two others were injured ,","depth":9},{"id":111,"text":"possibly by glass shattering from gunshot blasts .","depth":9},{"id":112,"text":"Anne Arundel Medical Center confirmed","depth":10},{"id":113,"text":"two patients were brought there from the shooting .","depth":10},{"id":114,"text":"They had only minor injuries ,","depth":10},{"id":115,"text":"not caused by gunfire .","depth":10},{"id":116,"text":"One patient was discharged","depth":9},{"id":117,"text":"and the second was expected to be discharged in the morning .","depth":9},{"id":118,"text":"Police had blocked off the apartment building","depth":10},{"id":119,"text":"where Mr. Ramos lived","depth":10},{"id":120,"text":"as they conducted their investigation Thursday night .","depth":9},{"id":121,"text":"John Cusumano ,","depth":12},{"id":122,"text":"who lived in the building ,","depth":12},{"id":123,"text":"said","depth":11},{"id":124,"text":"Mr. Ramos kept to himself ,","depth":11},{"id":125,"text":"and neighbors didn ' t even know","depth":13},{"id":126,"text":"if he had a job","depth":13},{"id":127,"text":"because they rarely saw him leave .","depth":12},{"id":128,"text":"\" He played a lot of war video games","depth":11},{"id":129,"text":"because you can hear the shooting","depth":12},{"id":130,"text":"when you did laundry , \"","depth":12},{"id":131,"text":"Mr. Cusumano said .","depth":10},{"id":132,"text":"\" My thoughts and prayers are with the victims and their families .","depth":10},{"id":133,"text":"Thank you to all of the First Responders","depth":11},{"id":134,"text":"who are currently on the scene , \"","depth":11},{"id":135,"text":"he tweeted .","depth":9},{"id":136,"text":"First lady Melania Trump and other White House staffers also offered their prayers and condolences .","depth":10},{"id":137,"text":"Everyone","depth":14},{"id":138,"text":"who spoke with The Times","depth":14},{"id":139,"text":"spoke of how safe Annapolis is","depth":13},{"id":140,"text":"and used the word \" shocked \"","depth":13},{"id":141,"text":"to describe how the shooting punctuated the normally quiet community .","depth":13},{"id":142,"text":"Rodolfo Beltren ,","depth":15},{"id":143,"text":"who has lived in the Annapolis area for the past 15 years","depth":16},{"id":144,"text":"and drives full time for Lyft ,","depth":16},{"id":145,"text":"said","depth":14},{"id":146,"text":"he ferried home employees from the buildings","depth":14},{"id":147,"text":"after the police interviewed all 170 evacuated workers .","depth":14},{"id":148,"text":"They were in shock ,","depth":14},{"id":149,"text":"Mr. Beltren said ,","depth":14},{"id":150,"text":"and all asked the same question :","depth":14},{"id":151,"text":"\" How can something like that happen in Annapolis ?","depth":15},{"id":152,"text":"To the Capital ? \"","depth":15},{"id":153,"text":"The shooting prompted wild speculation from anti-Trump figures","depth":11},{"id":154,"text":"who blamed the president ,","depth":12},{"id":155,"text":"saying","depth":13},{"id":156,"text":"his criticism of the press had created an environment","depth":14},{"id":157,"text":"that fueled the shooting .","depth":14},{"id":158,"text":"The Baltimore Sun said","depth":13},{"id":159,"text":"police officers had responded to that paper ' s headquarters as a precaution against another attack .","depth":13},{"id":160,"text":"The New York Police Department also confirmed","depth":14},{"id":161,"text":"it dispatched officers to media outlets in that city .","depth":14},{"id":162,"text":"\" These deployments are not based on specific threat information ,","depth":16},{"id":163,"text":"but rather out of an abundance of caution","depth":17},{"id":164,"text":"until we learn more about the suspect and motives behind the Maryland shooting , \"","depth":17},{"id":165,"text":"said Deputy Commissioner for Counterterrorism and Intelligence John Millie .","depth":15},{"id":166,"text":"\" It has become standard practice to shift resources strategically during active shooter or active terrorist events , \"","depth":15},{"id":167,"text":"he said .","depth":15},{"id":168,"text":"A spokeswoman for the Metropolitan Police Department in D.C. declined to say","depth":13},{"id":169,"text":"whether they would follow suit","depth":13},{"id":170,"text":"but urged people to report any suspicious activity .","depth":12},{"id":171,"text":"- Dave Boyer , Laura Kelly and Ben Wolfgang contributed to this article .","depth":1}],"relations":[{"parent":343,"left":342,"right":171,"relation"